The teaching staff at WAY Michigan has created projects for Constitution Day. There is one project for High School students and one for Middle School Students. The High School project has two modules. The first module looks at the United States Constitution and its importance. The second module compares the United States Constitution to other constitutions around the world. High School students can earn credit in Civics and English for completing the project successfully. Find the link on our website to start working on the project.

post_text:
WAY Schools allow students to explore authentic, engaging, and real-world problems through Project-Based Learning. But what exactly is it?

While so many schools are trying to break free from the traditional school culture set in place centuries ago, there is still a struggle to find the right fit. The misconception is that PBL is just like "doing a project" but it's much more than that! In project based learning, the learning comes alive for students and they are engaged in a project over a period of time solving real world problems and responding to authentic, complex and engaging questions.

This is what we do at WAY and this is why our students are so successful! Join us and find your success this new school year! Enroll now for the 2020-21 school year at WAY Academy! More information at http://wayacademy.net
Find other WAY Program schools at http://wayprogram.net

#wayprogram #wayacademy #michigan #detroit #enrollnow #schoolyear #backtoschool
--

"Clearly there are issues of equity and all hands should be on deck, both public and private, to assure all children get the education they need and deserve during this trying time. There are proven alternatives, that with desire and creativity can be put into action to continue learning. That is exactly what we at W-A-Y are committed to doing."

post_text:
What exactly is Project Based Learning? While so many schools are trying to break free from the traditional school culture set in place centuries ago, there is still a struggle to find the right fit. The misconception is that PBL is just like "doing a project" but it's much more than that! In project based learning, the learning comes alive for students and they are engaged in a project over a period of time solving real world problems and responding to authentic, complex and engaging questions.

This is what we do at WAY and this is why our students are so successful!

Do you know the Five Requirements of a WAY Michigan Researcher? Here they are!

1. Contact their mentor 3-5 times per week.
2. Earn 0.5 credit each month.
3. Log into HERO and work on projects six hours a day, five days a week, totaling 30 hours a week.
4. Attend Count Day and complete requirements in October and February.
5. Participate in State and Charter-authorized testing.

For more information, call 313.638.2716 or visit: waymichigan.net

post_text:
GET YOUR CREDITS IN NOW!!!
All Researchers: You are required to earn .5 credits per month. December is no different and is a tough month, because many of you believe you get two weeks off. Understand we will still hold all of you to the minimum credit requirement. Also, we (central office staff) are not working the last nine days of December, so we will not be there to push for you to take tests, do a live session (none scheduled during break), yell at you to turn something in, etc. It is to your benefit to do your 5-6 projects now, and then relax the last part of December.
